The experimental design of the first stage of testing was generated according to uniform design theory.[

59

] 72 combinations were chosen with the largest sum of multi‐drug interaction distances and smallest variance of accumulative doses from trillions of randomly generated experiment designs. The design of the second stage of validation was generated according to orthogonal array design (OAD).
